{
  "stem": "14251.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And my mother tried to say to them-- I don't know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Remember, we couldn't talk Russian.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "She knew some snippets of Polish from having had Polish help in the region where she was born.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They employed a lot of Polish people who had stayed in the regions, just like the German Jews stayed in the region when it was Polish some of the time.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But that doesn't mean you speak their language.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "There was always a language difference.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And then suddenly she remembered a word, being called that by the Polish children, and it was Zhid, which is an later supposedly forbidden term for Jew for the-- for the Russians, happens to be the same word.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Many of their words are the same.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But it had not too much effect, it turned out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "They did take her, though, to their headquarter man, and it luckily was that he happened to be a Russian Jew from Kazakhstan.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And he said, I'll try to help you all I can, but all Jews are dead.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "My mother said, no, no, no, no, no.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I have to explain to you.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I have to get back to Berlin, I have to, and so on.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And this was conducted in half German-- well, she could only do the German.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "He didn't know any other languages.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And he poked along in his Yiddish and told us that he came from a region where the women were veiled-- some other world altogether-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] [?",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Samarkand ?] or someplace.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I don't know, regions that were remote.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And he said, you know, it's not going to be safe for all you people here.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And she tried to explain these people had saved us, and we wanted them to be treated well.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
